        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2371225460" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8392378890876988961">We Are Called to Rise was a bit hit and miss for me. <br/>I loved the opening chapter. Avis steals across the bedroom, naked, in the dark, about to surprise her husband, when his voice stills her with some devastating news, news she doesn’t want to hear.<br/>This was a fantastic opening and made me think I was in for a fab read. <br/>However, after this first chapter I felt the book chopped and changed with new characters being introduced constantly. I was a quarter into the book before I settled into the read</span>
  <span id="freeText8392378890876988961" style="display:none">We Are Called to Rise was a bit hit and miss for me. <br />I loved the opening chapter. Avis steals across the bedroom, naked, in the dark, about to surprise her husband, when his voice stills her with some devastating news, news she doesn’t want to hear.<br />This was a fantastic opening and made me think I was in for a fab read. <br />However, after this first chapter I felt the book chopped and changed with new characters being introduced constantly. I was a quarter into the book before I settled into the read. <br />There is a failing marriage, domestic abuse, veteran rehabilitation, PTSD, police violence and immigration..... all the elements are there for a great story but for me, it did not fully click into a fully rounded book. <br />The ending was so abrupt and left me feeling ... well....nothing much ☹️<br />We Are Called to Rise was good in places but for me it didn’t live up to its potential.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8392378890876988961" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
