        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer960073507" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3757729966793824931">What a powerful book. I&apos;m left feeling raw and holding onto the sliver of hope that the book has instilled in my heart. I wish I would&apos;ve read this book at another time in my life, because I feel that it would have impacted me more than it already did. I look forward to a re-read down the road. <br/><br/>Tough subject matter relating to PTSD suffered by soldiers fighting in Iraq. The book all the way around is depressing and filled with horrifying and tragic events. Still the author brilliantly sews the s</span>
  <span id="freeText3757729966793824931" style="display:none">What a powerful book. I'm left feeling raw and holding onto the sliver of hope that the book has instilled in my heart. I wish I would've read this book at another time in my life, because I feel that it would have impacted me more than it already did. I look forward to a re-read down the road. <br /><br />Tough subject matter relating to PTSD suffered by soldiers fighting in Iraq. The book all the way around is depressing and filled with horrifying and tragic events. Still the author brilliantly sews the stories together into one and offers a grim reality all too real for too many of our soldiers coming home. Couldn't recommend this one to every reader, but for those willing to dig deep, this one is well worth it.</span>
